        <h2>Role of Operational Managers</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Project Planning and Execution</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers are involved in the
              planning and execution of solar projects. They work closely with
              project teams, stakeholders, and clients to define project scopes,
              timelines, and deliverables. They ensure that projects are
              executed within budget and meet quality standards.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Resource Allocation and Management</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers allocate resources such as
              personnel, equipment, and materials to various projects. They
              ensure that the right resources are available at the right time,
              optimizing efficiency and productivity. They also manage
              subcontractors and vendors, fostering strong partnerships.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Quality Control and Compliance</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers enforce strict quality
              control measures to ensure that all solar installations and
              services meet industry standards and regulatory requirements. They
              establish and monitor quality assurance processes, conduct
              inspections, and address any issues that may arise.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Budgeting and Cost Control</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers are responsible for
              budgeting and cost control for solar projects. They develop
              project budgets, track expenses, and manage costs throughout the
              project lifecycle. They analyze financial data, identify
              cost-saving opportunities, and make informed decisions to optimize
              project profitability.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Risk Management</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers identify and mitigate
              risks associated with solar projects. They assess potential risks,
              develop contingency plans, and implement risk management
              strategies to minimize project disruptions and ensure smooth
              operations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Team Leadership and Development</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers lead and motivate project
              teams, providing guidance, support, and performance feedback. They
              foster a collaborative and positive work environment, promoting
              professional growth and development of team members.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Client Relationship Management</h5>
            <p class="card-text">Operational managers maintain strong
              relationships with clients, ensuring clear communication,
              understanding client requirements, and addressing any concerns.
              They strive to exceed client expectations, fostering long-term
              partnerships and generating repeat business.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
